write a python function to read from an excel spreadsheet.
Here's a Python function that reads data from an Excel spreadsheet using the pandas library.
```python
import pandas as pd

# Read the Excel spreadsheet into a Pandas DataFrame
df = pd.read_excel("spreadsheet.xlsx")

# Print the first row of the DataFrame
print(df.head())
```
This function reads the data from the `spreadsheet.xlsx` file and creates a Pandas DataFrame with the data. It then prints the first row of the DataFrame using the `head()` method.
